PBG’s Szkudlarczyk Says Dividend From 2011 Profit Won’t Increase

-- B y   N a t h a n i e l   E s p i n o
-- 
2011-09-28T08:34:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-28/pbg-s-szkudlarczyk-says-dividend-from-2011-profit-won-t-increase.html
PBG SA (PBG)  won’t pay a higher dividend
from 2011 profit than the 20 million zloty it paid from last
year’s income, and the board will decide in about six months
whether to recommend a payout at all, Przemyslaw Szkudlarczyk,
chief financial officer of  Poland ’s third-largest construction
company, said in an interview with TVN CNBC television today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Nathaniel Espino at 
 nespino@bloomberg.net  